description:
Conclusion to the "15 Minutes" storyline.

The Gen13 team strikes back at the heart of their tormentors. I.O.'s 15 minutes is up!!! They wanted to be left alone and start new lives, but I.O. just did not listen....their mistake! It's time for Caitlin, Roxy, Bobby, Sarah, Eddie and their new Gen-Active friends to take down the entire operation. But when the time comes, can they make the jump into the unknown to take down ALL of I.O. and not just the division that has been following them?
name: 15 Minutes Part 7

description:
Look before you leap! After jumping through an I.O. teleportation device at the close of their last adventure, the Gen13 kids find themselves in a radically changed world that they NEVER expected! The fallout from Number of the Beast continues as the epic "Teenage Wasteland" begins!

Lynch: One Last Thing, Part 3
name: Teenage Wasteland, Part 1 - Siege Perilous

description: All of the secrets and lies being used to mess with the team is out in the open. I.O.'s plan has failed, all that's left is to terminate Gen13. Some unexpected help and hindrances will shape this showdown, can the kids liberate themselves from I.O.'s clutches forever?
name: 15 Minutes Part 6

description: Green Arrow meets Superman to find out who was at his funeral. He sees photos of many old friends but mysteriously Catman also attended his funeral. He decides to find out what was the man's motivation and uses Roy's help to track him down.
name: The Archer's Quest Chapter One: Photograph

description: Arsenal finds out that Green Arrow had trusted Shade with collecting Ollie's belongings when he died. And Oliver finds out that Shade failed to collect some of his belongings. Oliver starts his search for the remainder of his items at the Arrowcave.
name: The Archer's Quest Chapter Two: Grays of Shade

description: Green Arrow and Arsenal vs Solomon Grundy.
name: The Archer's Quest Chapter Three: Grundy No Like Arrows in Face!

description: The Archer's Quest continues as Green Arrow sneaks into the Watchtower and the Flash Museum to find the things he left behind before his death.
name: The Archer's Quest Chapter Four: Superfriends

description: After a chance encounter with Thomas Blake, Ollie and Roy make their last stop on their Quest: Ferris Aircraft.
name: The Archer's Quest Chapter Five: Kryptonite

description:
Best-selling novelist Brad Meltzer saved the biggest surprise of "The Archer's Quest" for last! This is what it's all been leading up to. Why has Green Arrow been on this quest? Not for the reasons you think!

In the conclusion to Archer's Quest the real reason behind Ollie gathering up the last of his possessions from before his death is revealed.
name: The Archer's Quest Conclusion: Fatherhood

description: A stand-alone story written by Scott Beatty (BATMAN: GOTHAM KNIGHTS)! Count Vertigo has a bone to pick with his ol' arch(er) rival, Green Arrow! It's a showdown in the tropics, as the two battle it out on primordial turf. What does a cigar-smoking skeleton have to do with it all?
name: The Vertigo Treatment

description:
They're not the Russian Mafia, they're aliens, but what are they doing? And can Ollie and Kyle overcome past grudges and keep it together long enough to stop these aliens?

Ollie breaks up what appears to be a drug run in Star City, but it turns out that the gang bangers were just transporting large amounts of bleach.

In New York, while out with Jade and some of her co-workers, Kyle sees what he believes is a drug deal gone wrong. He saves one guy but is knocked out when mysterious woman blasts him with a ray gun.

Jade is able to catch two of the dealers who reveal to Jade and Kyle that they are really aliens before transporting away.

Kyle is able to track their transport trail to Star City where he meets up with Ollie at the hangout of the gang that Ollie stopped earlier. The two heroes argue over whose bust this is, and get in a fist fight.

The gang bangers take this opportunity to escape where they run into the aliens from New York. The heroes hear a scream and find the gang bangers body charred in the alleyway.
name: Busted

description:
Green Arrow and Green Lantern are mystified when a lookalike of Hal Jordan's predecessor appears! What does this character have to do with Abin Sur and the original Green Lantern Corps? All they know is that this may be their only chance to get the upper hand on the intergalactic criminals known only as the Black Circle!

Kyle Rayner gets a call from Connor Hawke to come to Star City, quick. When he gets there Ollie and Connor introduce him to Amon Sur, Abin Sur's son.

Amon Sur links with Kyle's ring to explain he is part of Special Police Force and he is tracking the Black Circle, a crime syndicate, to earth and he needs help stopping them from getting a foot hold on Earth.

Ollie, Connor and Kyle agree to go to Amon's ship and get some tracking equipment, when they get to the ship they are ambushed by a bounty hunter working for the Black Circle. Ollie is shot but not badly wounded.

Before they can question the bounty hunter he blows up. Kyle and Amon Sur fly into space to try and stop an exchange, but are ambushed by a cloaked Black Circle ship.

Ollie tries to track the Black Circle in Star City but he too is ambushed and left for dead.
name: Hero Worship

description:
The Mafia will shoot anything that moves! The intergalactic menace of the Black Circle will kill anyone without remorse! And the police have their backs against the wall! Enter Green Arrow and Green Lantern, just in time to find Connor and Black Canary caught in the crossfire! Meanwhile, something's gone sour within the Black Circle…as if this intergalactic organization of crime weren't already rotten enough!

Green Arrow and Green Lantern are questioning a Black Circle goon but get little information out of him, other then the fact that his group has splintered off from the Black Circle and is trying to claim Earth. Then it comes over the police radio there is a shoot out between the Mafia of Star City and the aliens and the police are caught in the middle.

Green Arrow and Green Lantern show up in time to see Connor Hawke and Black Canary get things under control.

When Kyle finds Amon Sur he witnesses him kill an alien in cold blood. When the rest of the group confront him he goes on a rant about Kyle being weak. But before he can say much more a Black Circle ship shows up and teleports Amon Sur away.

The heroes barely make it out of the way when the ship opens fire on them and warps away.

Kyle uses his ring to teleport him and green Arrow aboard the ship, but they find themselves trapped and quickly become knocked out by Amon Sur who works for the Black Circle.
name: Know Thy Enemy

description: "Straight Shooter" kicks off with Part 1 of 6 as new regular writer Judd Winick joins the best-selling art team of Phil Hester & Ande Parks and cover artist Matt Wagner! Star City is getting a facelift, but gentrification has its costs. Green Arrow has always been a man of the people, but now he has to prove it. Little does he know that he has to prove it against a 3-ton ogre! To top it off, Black Lightning is coming to Star City…but as a friend or foe?
name: Straight Shooter Part One: Hired Guns

description:
Police officers were attacked at the Elevast site, so cops are rounding up the likely suspects. Connor Hawke calls his friend, Dennis, who works in a morgue, the one where the police officer's bodies were taken. Connor and Ollie figure out it's a monster.

Meanwhile at Elevast, the CEO demands to have "it" destroyed, & they hire Constantine Drakon.

Joanna Pierce is over at Ollie's house, giving him an update on the building. Mia comes in and tells Ollie there is a leak in the stove again and not to forget to call Dinah. Later Ollie goes out and finds the monster that had the policemen. Just as he defeats the monster and goes to walk away and three more monsters appear.
name: Straight Shooter Part Two: Not In My Backyard

description: Ollie defeats the three monsters and brings one to Connor's friend, Dennis, at the morgue. Ollie gets an idea so he stops by Joanna's apartment to ask her about immigrants from Zimbabwe, Africa that Elevast brought over to work on the Star Center. Joanna patches Ollie's side that is bleeding. Joanna and Ollie sleep together. Connor calls Ollie and says he hasn't heard from Dennis recently. Ollie stops by the morgue, and finds Dennis dead and Constantine Drakon. Ollie tries to fight Drakon, but Drakon wins. Drakon sticks ollie to the floor by stabbing an arrow through each of his hands, telling Ollie the only reason he didn't kill Ollie was because he wasn't paid to.
name: Straight Shooter Part Three: Beasts of Burden

description:
Dinah calls Ollie, but Ollie tells her not to worry and to stay in Seattle.

Meanwhile, the CEO of Elevast tells Drakon he is unhappy with the sloppy manner of his work. Drakon says he will have to be payed more to deal with Green Arrow.

Connor and Ollie look at a e-mail Dennis sent them before he died. It confirmed Ollie's suspicions; the monsters were mutated immigrants from Zimbabwe, who were brought over on a work visa fro Elevast. Ollie and Joanna talk in the training room. Ollie tells Joanna that he is involved with someone and she knew that... but she didn't. Joanna leaves and unknown to Ollie Mia has been watching him.

Drakon sets a trap for the monsters, but Ollie manges to save one.
name: Straight Shooter Part Four: New Wounds

description:
Ollie takes the monster he saved to S.T.A.R. Labs, to run tests on it. Joanna says she has papers on Elevast's dealings. Connor tells Ollie that he realizes Ollie cheated on Dinah and that pisses him off. Ollie goes to try and talk to Mia but she says she has to study.

At Elevast the CEO is upset. Drakon says he will finish the job, and not to summon him again. Ollie arrives downtown to find lots of monsters running about. Superman stops in to help out.

The doctor from S.T.A.R. Labs tells Ollie the thing all of the infected have in common is that they had Tuberculosis inoculations from a company named Tepcorp. While telling Joanna this she tells Ollie to get over to her apartment right away. But when he arrives Joanna is hung from her ceiling.
name: Straight Shooter Part Five: Loose Ends

description: Joanna is dead, but before she died she sent a few e-mails about Tepcorp. Drakon is at Ollie's house and Connor faces him. And to stop Drakon Connor has to shoot an arrow through Mia's shoulder and blow up the kitchen. Elevast is unmaskeed, and the CEO is mysteriously killed. Jeff (Black Lightening) is upset with himself over the death of his niece.
name: Straight Shooter Part Six

description: Green Arrow recruits gangsters and police alike to make an attack on Albert Davis' house. Mia also joins the fight.
name: City Walls Part Five: Oliver's Army

description: The conclusion to the City Walls arc. Green Arrow leads an attack on Albert Davis' house with the police and gangsters. Oliver and Mia get inside Albert Davis' house, only to find that he wants to be killed because it is the only way to stop the demons. Mia kills Albert Davis.
name: City Walls Part Six: "...Come Tumbling Down..."

description: All seems peaceful after everything that had happened in the last few days, but Danny "Brick" Brickwell is gathering gang territory and recruiting more gang members. Meanwhile Green Arrow and Black Canary decide to stop seeing each other.
name: New Blood Part One: Moving Day

description: One of the last two refuges of humanity comes with horrible secrets.
name: Revelations

description: A bomb kills dozens and spreads terror throughout Green Arrow's hometown! Can Ollie take the mad bomber down before he strikes again?
name: Anarky in the USA

description: Ollie sends Zatanna to follow Mia around at school. Meanwhile Ollie recruits Black Lightening to help him find who blew up his house.
name: Identity Crisis... Again

description: Green Arrow assists Dr. Chrissie Cavendish in her quest to cure Solomon Grundy.
name: Family Relations

description: Dr. Light fights Kimiyo Hoshi (previously the hero Doctor Light), and takes her powers. Green Arrow and Black Lightning arrive at the hospital only to realized they walked into a trap, as Killer Frost and Mirror Master arrive.
name: Heading Into The Light Part One: His Name is My Name, Too.

description: Killer Frost and Mirror Master attack Green Arrow and Black Lightning at the hospital. Killer Frost reveals it was simply a diversion.
name: Heading Into The Light Part Two: Cold Reflections

description: On the trail of the unpredictable Dr. Light, Green Arrow and Black Lightning are sidetracked by an attack from Mirror Master and Killer Frost! But is the appearance of some old foes a coincidence or part of a more sinister plot?
name: Heading Into The Light Part Three: School's Out

description: Dr. Light enters Star City, his targets: Ollie, Conner, and Mia. Black Lightning has vowed to stand by the archer's side until the bitter end, but will it be enough stop the approaching wave of destruction?
name: Heading Into The Light Part Four: House Warming

description: Having viciously attacked his family and destroyed his home, the enemies of Green Arrow wage war against the whole of Star City! The Emerald Archer must defend his hometown from catastrophe while his allies lie beneath the tons of rubble that was once his headquarters .
name: Until the End of the World, Part One: Persistence is Futile

description: Arrow for arrow, bow versus bow, Green Arrow faces off against Merlyn; and in the balance lies the fate of Star City's millions of citizens! How many can the Emerald Archer save when at every turn another deadly explosion rocks his beloved hometown?
name: Until the End of the World, Part Two

description: A new WildStorm series debuts, tying into events of the new GEN13! Preston Kills has an incredible gift--a gift of second sight given to him by the mysterious Herod when Preston was a boy. There’s just one catch: the gift will kill Preston when he turns 21, meaning he has only an all-too-brief year left to live. When a mysterious woman appears at Preston’s door with the idea that he might be able to save himself, his world is turned upside-down!
name: The Conduit, Part 1: Simple Kind of Life

description: The new WildStorm series tying into events of the new GEN13 continues! Recruited by FBI Agent Mickey Rinaldi, Preston Kills reluctantly begins his quest to discover the origin of his powers and uncover the secret of the mysterious entity called Herod. But that quest into the wilds of suburbia may be over before it even begins when Mickey and Preston meet another of Herod's creations, Harmony, a young woman they find themselves, quite literally, willing to kill for.
name: The Conduit, Part 2: I Like to Wear Sheep's Clothing

description: The supernatural suspense continues as life becomes infinitely more complicated for Preston and Mickey. Simmering tensions between them are magnified by the approaching hour of Harmony's judgment. Alone in the forests of Bear Mountain, Preston struggles with the morality of his decision to help Mickey and the inevitable arrival of Herod. Will he be able to stop Herod from passing judgment or will Herod take him as well?
name: The Conduit, Part 3: I'm Not Sick, But I'm Not Well

description: In the wake of the terrifying events at Bear Mountain, Preston returns home with more questions than answers regarding Agent Mickey Rinaldi and her Genie initiative. Seeking the advice of his friend Sam, Preston attempts to explain his problem when he receives an urgent call regarding another grisly murder, one that may be tied directly to Herod.
name: The Conduit, Part 4: Don't Stand Alone In These Strangest of Times

description:
Overview

Have things between Mickey and Preston gone too far? Will their moment of intimacy complicate the search for Herod, or is Preston merely a pawn in Mickey's game? Who or what is Test Subject 044 and what does it have to do with Mickey?
name: The Conduit Part 5: Distance From One Into the Other

description: "The Conduit" reaches its shocking conclusion as Preston and his brother Robert uncover the mystery behind the recent string of unsolved murders. In a terrifying showdown with the killer, Preston discovers that the Herod phenomenon affects more than just the people he touches.
name: The Conduit Part 6: End of Night

description: A new story arc and jumping-on point for new readers begins here! Join the adventures of Preston Kills, tattoo artist and reluctant super-hero, as he teams with rogue FBI agent Mickey Rinaldi in a desperate search to uncover the secret of Herod, a mysterious entity that grants super-powers to children...only to kill them on their 21st birthday.
name: Transitions

description:
Overview

"Roadside Attractions," Part 1 of 5. In the first installment of this new story arc, downtown Detroit is under siege from an angry weather god, while Mickey and Preston find themselves immersed in the mystery surrounding a young girl's disappearance. Strange things start to happen as Preston's powers begin growing in unexpected ways. With time running out, Preston must determine the connection among an eclipse, the number 19, and a mysterious ring of fire in order to save the missing girl!
name: Roadside Attractions Part 1

description: In their frantic search to find a missing girl, Mickey and Preston come face to face with the legendary war hero Hank Champion. What horrifying secrets drove America's most famous soldier into retirement...and will they survive the experience? Meanwhile, in the forests of Bear Mountain, New York, something long forgotten is feeding on ill-fated hikers!
name: Roadside Attractions Part 2: Emotional Landscapes

description: Check out the book Wizard magazine calls "a cross between Logan's Run and Seven!" Preston and Mickey face off against the physical manifestation of an American war hero's psychological trauma. Meanwhile, Mickey's daughter is traumatized by a horrific event and sets out to destroy her laboratory prison and exact deadly revenge on the mysterious man called Neptune!
name: Roadside Attractions Part 3: State of Emergency

description: "Roadside Attractions," Part 4. By all appearances, the town of Big Tuna, Texas is average...but strange, almost magical things are happening on its lonely backroads. Mickey and Preston have no idea that their time together is running out and death is lurking around every curve! Meanwhile, in a secret underground laboratory, Mickey's daughter Alex stares down The Company Man, a metahuman assassin unleashed to stop her at all costs!
name: Roadside Attractions Part 4: I Am the Highway

description: The astonishing conclusion to "Roadside Attractions!" Alex confronts a being claiming to be Herod. Mickey and Preston's lives are drastically transformed. And all of 21 DOWN undergoes a dramatic change! This issue's startling revelations and shocking secrets lay the groundwork for the upcoming second 21 DOWN series, as the same creative team takes the critically acclaimed series in a bold new direction!
name: Roadside Attractions Part 5: We Live in a Beautiful World

description: Will Azrael be able to stop a "Jokerized" Sister Lilhy before she commits a gruesome crime? And why has Lilhy decided to don her own version of the Azrael costume? Is this some kind of joke?
name: The Evil Men Do...

description: Having crash-landed in a South American jungle, Azrael befriends an unfortunate, misshapen monster called Calibax. What's more unfortunate is that Calibax is marked for death...at the hands of Deathstroke! It's Azrael versus Deathstroke for the life of a stranger!
name: Angel and the Beast: Deathstroke!

description: Part 1 of the 3-part “Prophet.” Azrael is sent back into the desert on a personal mission for Dr. Thompkins: find her brother and bring him back from the mysterious cult he may have joined! But is Leslie's brother the renegade cult's leader, Jeremiah? Plus, Lilhi's new Azrael returns!
name: Cry For Atonement

description: Part 2 of the 3-part "Prophet." Jean Paul's mission to the desert takes a grisly turn as he begins to learn the secrets of the strange new Azrael! Stripped of his powers, will the "Agent of the Bat" be able to thwart the other Azrael, who wears Jean Paul's former costume with all his abilities intact? And what role does Leslie Thompkins' brother play in all this?
name: Brothers

description: Part 3 of the 3-part “Prophet.” The confrontation between Jean-Paul Valley and a foe wearing his old costume continues! In Gotham City, Batman and Oracle begin to worry that Azrael has once again become a vengeful killing machine while, in a desert thousands of miles away, Jean-Paul struggles to free the new Azrael from his brainwashed state.
name: Hell & Back!

description: Batman confronts Azrael in Part 1 of a powerful 3-part story! The deadly new Azrael has come to Gotham City, with Jean Paul Valley close behind. Batman fears that Jean Paul may have returned to his murderous ways, but can Jean Paul prove otherwise before another innocent victim falls?
name: Homecoming

description: When a long-forgotten movie serial inspires a rash of grave robberies, only Azrael can get to the bottom of the crimes. Why is this movie so important to the criminals? And who is the secret mastermind behind their ghoulish deeds? Learn the shocking answer in "The Amazing Adventures of Captain Death!"
name: The Amazing Adventures of Captain Death

description: A DC FULL COVERAGE! entry-point issue! A new villain makes his debut as Azrael makes a startling discovery! When a crazed former soldier begins brutally executing policemen and other members of "the establishment" he deems evil, only Azrael stands a chance of stopping the rampage. But the results of their encounter have startling repercussions for both men. Plus, Jean Paul begins to experience a radical change.
name: The Sentinel

description: An assignment for Sister Lilhy leads Azrael to encounter a new foe. Will Jean Paul's mysteriously increased strength be enough to deal with a new metagene-enhanced menace?
name: Kenny

description: Nightwing guest-stars in an issue featuring the new cover art team of Mike Zeck & Jerry Ordway! Oracle has information about Azrael's mysteriously increased strength, information that will change his life forever, but she doesn't know where he is. Unbeknownst to her, Jean Paul is in a fight for his life with a vengeance-crazed metahuman. Will Nightwing be able to find Azrael before the fight is finished?
name: Lost and Found

description: Batman guest stars as Azrael, with a mob of supporters at his side, leads a siege against Two-Face! Azrael's super-powered, newly violent ways are beginning to exact a heavy price. Now the Dark Knight, feeling responsible for all that Jean Paul has become, swears to take him down...by any means necessary. Say your prayers!
name: The White Place

description: Catch up on what's been going on with Daredevil since Ed Brubaker's been writing.
